    <!-- Add Activity -->

     <activity>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                <alert>Work in groups</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                A group of Grade 11 students are asked to design a formula for a construction company. 
                The company builds rectangular foundations of many different sizes, but the math is always the same: <m>ax^2 + bx + c = 0</m>.
            </p>
            <p>
                Instead of completing the square from scratch every single day, which takes too long and leads to mistakes, 
                the boss wants a single formula where they can just plug in the numbers (<m>a, b,</m> and <m>c</m>) and get the dimensions of <m>x</m> immediately.
            </p>
            <p>
                <alert>What to do</alert>
            </p>
        </introduction>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                     For one of the foundation designs, the relationship between the measurements leads to the equation:
                     <m>3x^2 + 6x + 9 = 0</m>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Solve <m>3x^2 + 6x + 9 = 0</m> by completing the square, clearly  showing your steps.
                </p>
                
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Now, you need to derive a formula that will work for any rectangular foundation. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    Replace the specific numbers in the equation abovewith variables <m>a, b,</m> and <m>c</m> respectively.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Derive a formula for <m>x</m> in terms of <m>a, b,</m> and <m>c</m>.
                </p>
                
            </statement>
        </task>
        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                        Share your work with your fellow learners.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
        
    </activity> 

